WEBVTT

00:00.269 --> 00:01.553
Man:1 <i>All right, ten hours down</i>

00:01.600 --> 00:03.789
<i>and only three more to go.
I got this.</i>

00:03.866 --> 00:06.189
Man 2: <i>Seriously, just pull over
and get some sleep.</i>

00:06.263 --> 00:07.398
<i>This is crazy.</i>

00:07.485 --> 00:08.835
You want to know what's crazy?

00:08.892 --> 00:10.578
Letting Betty move to New York.

00:10.664 --> 00:12.024
Not stopping the woman I love

00:12.056 --> 00:13.814
from making the biggest
mistake of her life.

00:13.853 --> 00:16.757
<i>It actually sounds like Betty's
doing extremely well out there.</i>

00:16.840 --> 00:18.843
<i>I mean, it's been
four years, Gordy.</i>

00:18.968 --> 00:21.343
Yeah, four years I couldn't stop
thinking about her.

00:21.432 --> 00:23.851
<i>Dude, you and Betty
dated for, like, a month.</i>

00:24.001 --> 00:25.250
<i>If you show up on her doorstep,</i>

00:25.298 --> 00:27.156
<i>trust me,
you're gonna look insane.</i>

00:27.304 --> 00:29.125
Ah, you want to know
what's insane?

00:29.206 --> 00:31.445
Letting Betty go to New York.
That's insane.

00:31.508 --> 00:33.546
<i>Gordy, enough. You need sleep.</i>

00:33.629 --> 00:35.343
<i>You're starting to sound
like a lunatic.</i>

00:35.446 --> 00:37.670
Nah, that's just the sound
of love, my friend.

00:37.718 --> 00:39.184
<i>The sweet, sweet sound of...</i>

00:39.216 --> 00:41.516
oh! Oh, God!
<i>What? What's wrong?</i>

00:41.552 --> 00:42.652
<i>What's going on?</i>
Oh, my God!

00:42.686 --> 00:44.056
<i>Gordy, what's going on?</i>

00:44.088 --> 00:45.866
(yells)
<i>is everything all right?</i>

00:45.952 --> 00:47.082
It just fell from the sky

00:47.191 --> 00:48.921
like some damn bird
or something!

00:48.959 --> 00:50.219
<i>Gordy? Gordy?</i>

00:52.930 --> 00:55.360
<i>Gordy? Gordy!</i>

00:58.402 --> 01:01.702
<i>Gordy?!</i>

01:02.111 --> 01:03.729
<i>What the hell just happened?</i>

01:03.777 --> 01:05.236
<i>And do not tell me
that was the sound of love.</i>

01:05.284 --> 01:06.838
That was the sound of death.

01:09.658 --> 01:11.879
Tell mama I just
crashed her car.

01:13.580 --> 01:14.776
Oh...

01:15.603 --> 01:18.073
Oh!

01:21.125 --> 01:24.795
Brennan: The victim jumped
30 feet off an overpass

01:25.000 --> 01:27.398
and landed on a passing car.

01:27.464 --> 01:28.794
Booth: That's
gonna leave a dent.

01:28.875 --> 01:31.359
I imagine it would
and given the, uh,

01:31.407 --> 01:33.819
gravitational acceleration rate
of 9.8 meters per...

01:33.867 --> 01:35.164
Ah, come on, Bones.
It's too early for math.

01:35.211 --> 01:36.969
Too early.
It's never too early for math.

01:37.017 --> 01:38.461
Anything before
12:00 is too early,

01:38.515 --> 01:39.665
anything after
12:00 is too late.

01:39.712 --> 01:40.877
That leaves no time for math.

01:40.911 --> 01:42.441
I don't want math.
I want math.

01:42.479 --> 01:43.909
It's way too early.

01:43.947 --> 01:45.887
Hey, take a look there,
that's Dr. Mayer, right?

01:45.916 --> 01:47.616
Brennan:
Oh, Dr. Mayer!

01:47.719 --> 01:49.336
It's so nice to see you again.

01:49.430 --> 01:50.555
Oh, Dr. Brennan!

01:50.621 --> 01:52.321
Agent Booth.

01:52.422 --> 01:54.875
What a treat. Please, join me.

01:54.951 --> 01:57.062
Uh, well, we-we got some food
to go, so...

01:57.154 --> 01:59.124
I got to get Boneshere
back to the lab.

01:59.196 --> 02:00.445
You're wearing your
jeffersonian lanyard.

02:00.492 --> 02:01.564
Are you coming in

02:01.612 --> 02:03.109
to help I.D.
The jumper?

02:03.185 --> 02:05.955
Actually,
I've hung up my lab coat.

02:06.072 --> 02:08.719
I never thought of you
as one to retire.

02:08.806 --> 02:10.203
Oh, heavens no.

02:10.274 --> 02:12.226
I woke up one morning and...

02:12.309 --> 02:14.649
Just found
the passion was missing.

02:15.858 --> 02:17.264
Well,
if you're not working anymore,

02:17.327 --> 02:19.032
why are you wearing
your jeffersonian badge?

02:19.079 --> 02:22.108
I'm studying prairie dogs
with the zoology department.

02:22.207 --> 02:23.600
Prairie dogs?

02:23.683 --> 02:26.686
Oh, actually, they're
fascinating little creatures.

02:26.944 --> 02:30.296
Did you know
their entire mating window

02:30.447 --> 02:33.249
is one hour a year?
(chuckles)

02:33.383 --> 02:35.804
by "fascinating,"
you mean "sad," right?

02:35.875 --> 02:37.139
(laughs)

02:37.234 --> 02:40.163
uh, congratulations
on your new career path.

02:40.270 --> 02:42.186
You seem... You seem happy.

02:42.288 --> 02:44.232
Sometimes it just takes
a new match

02:44.274 --> 02:46.358
to get the old flame
burning again.

02:46.478 --> 02:49.100
(laughs) tell that
to the prairie dogs, huh?

02:49.148 --> 02:50.319
(Mayer laughs)

02:50.415 --> 02:52.264
okay, got to go.
Let's go, Bones.

02:52.319 --> 02:54.397
Bye.
Thank you, Doll.

02:54.889 --> 02:57.115
Hodgins: Ooh, okay,
how about "Hulk Bones:

02:57.154 --> 02:59.124
"A study on the skeletal effects

02:59.156 --> 03:00.926
of incredible physical
strength."

03:00.957 --> 03:02.172
that's a great idea, Hodgins.

03:02.220 --> 03:03.570
Unfortunately,
to write that paper,

03:03.617 --> 03:04.820
I would need hulk's Bones.

03:04.868 --> 03:06.792
And since the Hulk
doesn't actually exist...

03:06.900 --> 03:08.547
Trust me,
your dissertation committee,

03:08.598 --> 03:09.922
they're gonna eat it up.
It's gonna prove

03:09.954 --> 03:11.898
that you can think
outside the box. Or,

03:11.970 --> 03:13.477
that you've completely
lost your mind.

03:13.599 --> 03:15.017
Brennan: Mr. Bray,
please catch me up

03:15.064 --> 03:16.894
on what you've discovered
thus far.

03:17.140 --> 03:19.273
Based on the size
of the femoral head

03:19.343 --> 03:21.398
coupled with the strong
torsion of the femoral neck,

03:21.478 --> 03:23.234
the victim was a Caucasian male.

03:23.313 --> 03:24.578
Brennan: Well,
excellent work,

03:24.641 --> 03:26.352
given the condition
of the remains.

03:26.483 --> 03:28.258
Burnt, broken,
and cut to ribbons.

03:28.306 --> 03:29.313
Well, if he wanted
to kill himself,

03:29.360 --> 03:31.164
he certainly
accomplished his goal.

03:31.409 --> 03:33.391
Our victim did not want
to kill himself.

03:33.502 --> 03:35.180
Well, according to
the police report,

03:35.228 --> 03:36.578
he jumped off an overpass.

03:36.727 --> 03:39.055
The fractures on the
skull are dry breaks.

03:39.186 --> 03:41.067
Which means he was actually dead
before he fall.

03:41.148 --> 03:42.500
This was a murder

03:42.585 --> 03:44.914
made to look like a suicide.

03:45.235 --> 03:47.094
♪ ♪

03:47.231 --> 03:51.853
